      "writtenOn": "2026-02-25T15:42:06Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Matt mentioned offline that a newer C++ method for printing output that is preferred is use of std::print and std::println. That supports substitution parameters like std::format, and the latter adds a newline to the end.\n\ne.g.\n\n```\nstd::println(\"\");\nstd::println(\"Chassis {}:\", chassisNumber);\nstd::print(\"    Present: \");\nstd::println(\"{}\", (chassis.isPresent() \u003d\u003d 1 ? \"True\" : \"False\"));\n...\nstd::println(stderr, \"       {}\", e.what());\n```",
      "revId": "8b41adf34d2011f8dd03f46da9cc55a65aeff9fc",
